The Mexican Institute of Health Insurance (IMSS) has announced that it is conducting research to detect the gene that causes obesity in children and the young. Research called "Abre Obesity Genetics in Children and Teenagers" will make it possible to obtain overweight results.
In a report by the head of the Biochemistry Research Unit in Biochemistry from the Specialized Hospital of the 21st Century National Health Center, Miguel Cruz López, he explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers had been set up.
